You will need to create a database.yml file. The one used in our production environment has been removed for obvious reasons =)

DO NOT add bugs to the database migration files

Note the Model People and User refer to the same table. If you use person.create, then you don't need to have a password on the box (ie using webiso authentication) if you use user.create, then you do need to have a password to have that row exist in the database.




